2)  Consider the following interface:

-----------------------------------------------------
public interface Greetings{

  public String FormalHello();
  
  public String CasualHello();
  
}
-----------------------------------------------------

a)  Explain what an interface is.
    An interface is a class which can be used as a base for another class. It holds variables and methods that the class whic uses the interface should have.
b)  Write a complete class for a language speaker of your choice, like ItalianSpeaker, which fully implements the interface.

public class GermanSpeaker implements Greetings {

    @Override
    public String FormalHello() {
        return "Guten Tag!";
    }

    @Override
    public String CasualHello() {
        return "Moin!";
    }
}
